40|$|An {{electromagnetic}} macroscopic modelling of CNT is derived. The conduction electrons of the nanotube {{are considered}} as a 2 D fluid moving on the surface representing the positive <b>ion</b> <b>lattice.</b> The linearized Euler’s equation describing the fluid motion {{is used as a}} macroscopic constitutive relationship to be coupled to Maxwell’s equation. A surface integral formulation coupled to the fluid model is solved numerically using a finite element method. For peculiar configurations, transmission line-like parameters of CNTs are derived...|$|E
